# What is Networking

## Goal
   Intro about the notion of Networking and how it applies in our modern world

## Summary
   A Networking is two or more systems echanging informations (like devices connected).
   The Internet is one giant network that consists of many small networks within itself. I was created by Tim Berners-Lee in 1989 as World Wide Web (www.).
   This small networks are called private networks, and private networks are connected by public networks (aka the Internet).
   There are 2 ways to identify a device : through it's IP adress and it's MAC adress.

## Notions
   ARPAnet (Advanced Research Projects Agency Network) project is the first network launched in the US by the DARPA (Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency) in 1966 and ended in 1990.
   IP adress, short for Internet Protocol (the name of the device). 
      Each device has 2 IP, one for public networks and one for private networks. 
      Public IP adresses are given by our Internet Service Provider (ISP), and used to identify the device on the internet.
      Private adress is used to be identify amongst other devices.
      IP adresses are devided into tour octets.
      The number calculated through the technique IP "adressing & subnetting".
      Can change from device to device.
      Cannot be active simultaneously on the same network.
      First version of the Internet Protocol IPv4, using the numbering system 2^32 IP adresses (~ 4.29 billion).
      Second version of the Internet Protocol IPv6, 2^128 IP adresses (340 trillion-plus) and more efficient.
         ex : IPv4 : 86.157.52.21
              IPv6 : 2001:0db8:85a3:0000:0000:8a2e:0370:7334
      IPv1-3 and 5 stayed experimentals 
   MAC adress, short for Media Access Control adress (the fingerprint of the device, similar to a serial number).
      Devices on a network will all have a physical network interface, a microchip board found on the device's motherboard.
      This interface is assigned a unique adress MAC.
      Twelve characters hexadecimal (based sixteen). The six first characters represent the company that made the network, six last are unique.
         ex : a4:c3:f0:85:ac:2d
   Firewall is a security toll, hardware or software, used to filter unauthorized traffic in the network
   Ping uses ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol)
   
